<section xml:id="sec-Linear-inequalities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Linear Inequalities</title>

  <introduction>

    <p>
      A linear inequality is a statement that compares two linear expressions using symbols such as:
    </p>

    <p>
      <me>\text{Less than} \rightarrow \quad (\lt)</me>
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <me>\text{Greater than} \rightarrow \, (\gt)</me>
    </p>

    <p>
      <me>\text{Less than or equal to} \rightarrow \, (\le)</me>  
    </p>

    <p>
      <me>\text{Greater than or equal to} \rightarrow \, (\ge)</me>
    </p>

    <p>
    These inequalities express a range of possible values rather than just one specific solution.
    </p>
  </introduction>

